      {
        "key": "2020111605450547000_2020.11.12.380196v1.27",
        "unstructured": "For example, if WASP-D is used to decontaminate books, a single book might take three hours to reach 43\u00b0C in a 46\u00b0C room, while a stack of books (due to the insulation value of cellulosic paper) might take ten hours or more. These heating time delays must be added to the 12-hour WASP-D cycle."
